#define PR(x) cout << #x " = " << x << "\n";
int days[13]={0,31,28,31,30,31,30,31,31,30,31,30,31};

int main(int argc, char const *argv[])
{
	int t,d,y; cin>>t;
	char m1,m2,m3;
	map<string, int> month;
	month["JAN"]=1;
	month["FEB"]=2;
	month["MAR"]=3;
	month["APR"]=4;
	month["MAY"]=5;
	month["JUN"]=6;
	month["JUL"]=7;
	month["AUG"]=8;
	month["SEP"]=9;
	month["OCT"]=10;
	month["NOV"]=11;
	month["DEC"]=12;
	int count=1;
	while(t--)
	{
		string m;
		scanf("%d-%c%c%c-%d",&d, &m1, &m2, &m3, &y);
		m.push_back(m1);
		m.push_back(m2);
		m.push_back(m3);
		// PR(d)
		// PR(m1)
		// PR(m2)
		// PR(m3)
		// PR(y)
		if (y%400==0 || (y%4==0 && y%100!=0))
		{
			days[2]=29;
		}
		else days[2]=28;
		int sum=0;
		for (int i = 1; i < month[m]; ++i) sum+=days[i];
		sum+=d;
		if (sum<=300)
		{
			printf("Case %d: %d Hundreds\n", count, sum);
		}
		else if(sum<=360)
		{
			printf("Case %d: %d Tens\n", count, sum-300);
			
		}
		else printf("Case %d: %d Ones\n",count, sum-360 );
		count++;
	}
	return 0;
}
